Kolmogorov tower (<a class=3D"ltx_ref" href=3D"https://arxiv.org/html/2507.=
21192v1#S2.E3" title=3D"In 2.1 Textbook Stochastic Processes =E2=80=A3 2 St=
ochastic Processes =E2=80=A3 Quantum Systems as Indivisible Stochastic Proc=
esses"><span class=3D"ltx_text ltx_ref_tag">3</span></a>) that trivializes
after <math alttext=3D"n" class=3D"ltx_Math" display=3D"inline" id=3D"S2.SS=
1.p13.m1"><semantics><mi>n</mi><annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">n=
</annotation><annotation encoding=3D"application/x-llamapun">italic_n</anno=
tation></semantics></math> orders, for some finite integer <math alttext=3D=
"n" class=3D"ltx_Math" display=3D"inline" id=3D"S2.SS1.p13.m2"><semantics><=
mi>n</mi><annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">n</annotation><annotati=
on encoding=3D"application/x-llamapun">italic_n</annotation></semantics></m=
ath>. Such a stochastic
process is said to be <em class=3D"ltx_emph ltx_font_italic"><math alttext=
=3D"n" class=3D"ltx_Math" display=3D"inline" id=3D"S2.SS1.p13.m3"><semantic=
s><mi>n</mi><annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">n</annotation><annot=
ation encoding=3D"application/x-llamapun">italic_n</annotation></semantics>=
</math>th-order non-Markovian</em>. A Markov
process corresponds to the case <math alttext=3D"n=3D1" class=3D"ltx_Math" =
display=3D"inline" id=3D"S2.SS1.p13.m4"><semantics><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>=3D<=
/mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">n=3D1</anno=
tation><annotation encoding=3D"application/x-llamapun">italic_n =3D 1</anno=
tation></semantics></math>. Newtonian mechanics, viewed
as a deterministic version of a stochastic process, is second-order
non-Markovian, because Newton=E2=80=99s second law is a second-order differ=
ential
equation, so it requires specifying positions at the present time
and at a time infinitesimally in the past=E2=80=94although, in
practice, one instead specifies positions and velocities at just the
present time.</p><button class=3D"sr-only button" style=3D"display: none;">=
Report issue for preceding element</button>
