<div class=3D"ltx_para" id=3D"S3.SS2.p5">
<p class=3D"ltx_p">Although it may seem surprising that these time-dependen=
t changes
of phase have no physical effects, keep in mind the <em class=3D"ltx_emph l=
tx_font_italic">crucial</em>
fact that this gauge transformation will end up having downstream
effects on the definitions of various Hilbert-space ingredients ahead,
in just such a way that all empirical predictions will remain unchanged.<sp=
an class=3D"ltx_note ltx_role_footnote" id=3D"footnote11"><sup class=3D"ltx=
_note_mark">11</sup><span class=3D"ltx_note_outer"><span class=3D"ltx_note_=
content"><sup class=3D"ltx_note_mark">11</sup><span class=3D"ltx_tag ltx_ta=
g_note">11</span>In particular, this form of gauge invariance is <em class=
=3D"ltx_emph ltx_font_italic">not</em> equivalent
to changing merely the relative phases of state vectors <em class=3D"ltx_em=
ph ltx_font_italic">alone</em>.</span></span></span></p><button class=3D"sr=
-only button" style=3D"display: none;">Report issue for preceding element</=
button>
</div>
<div class=3D"ltx_para" id=3D"S3.SS2.p6">
<p class=3D"ltx_p">This kind of gauge transformation will be called a <em c=
lass=3D"ltx_emph ltx_font_italic">Schur-Hadamard gauge transformation</em>,
because it involves the sort of entry-wise multiplication that characterize=
s
Schur or Hadamard products. To the author=E2=80=99s knowledge, this kind of
gauge invariance has not yet been described in the research literature,
and is therefore a new result. It will turn out to play a key role
in the analysis of dynamical symmetries that will be presented in
Subsection&nbsp;<a class=3D"ltx_ref" href=3D"https://arxiv.org/html/2507.21=
192v1#S4.SS1" title=3D"4.1 Dynamical Symmetries =E2=80=A3 4 Further Implica=
tions =E2=80=A3 Quantum Systems as Indivisible Stochastic Processes"><span =
class=3D"ltx_text ltx_ref_tag">4.1</span></a>, and will be extended
in an interesting way in the context of Hilbert-space dilations in
Subsection&nbsp;<a class=3D"ltx_ref" href=3D"https://arxiv.org/html/2507.21=
192v1#S4.SS2" title=3D"4.2 Dilations =E2=80=A3 4 Further Implications =E2=
=80=A3 Quantum Systems as Indivisible Stochastic Processes"><span class=3D"=
ltx_text ltx_ref_tag">4.2</span></a>. A different but equally general
form of gauge invariance will be discussed later on.</p><button class=3D"sr=
-only button" style=3D"display: none;">Report issue for preceding element</=
button>
</div>
</section>
